f=Cybersecurity/cortex/operational/skill/cortex-skill-routing.md В· h1:cortex Skill Routing Map=`в”Њв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ threat-hunting (proactive search в†’ findings) \В· в”‚                        в”‚ malicious в†’ IR \В· в”‚                        в”‚ suspicious в†’ new detection rules \В· в–ј \В· DETECTION в”Ђв–є detection-engineering (rules, SIEM tuning, false-positive mgmt)` В· h1:cortex Skill Routing Map=Non-leader (identity warden's). Law: ISMS security-inversion (cortex detects/recommends; operator contains/remediates). findings blind spots warden's register. **Handoffs:** warden (findings, logging gaps, incident lessons register risks) veil (regulatory notification clocks breach reporting) ops (joint security+reliability incidents coordinated IR) bastion (network anomalies feed network security reviews) board (material incidents escalate risk-acceptance threshold). **Precedence:** senior charters ISMS configs. cortex holds execute permissions detects, triages, recommends; operator contains remediates.